      "level": 1,
      "text": "Inspection of steering stationary operation load"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Stationary operation load Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "633_3.0_jpn_11293132_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Start the engine and confirm that the EPS warning light is off. If the EPS warning light does not turn off, Diagnose EPS system malfunctions. Park on a general asphalt surface. Attach a spring scale (A) to the steering wheel and pull it tangentially to the outer circumference of the steering wheel to read the stationary cut-off operation load when the tire begins to slide and move. Std. 31N (3.2kgf) or less",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "T001299",
          "label": "Diagnose EPS system malfunctions.",
          "resolved": true
        },
        {
          "id": "R000631",
          "label": "Inspect steering coupling",
          "resolved": true
        },
        {
          "id": "R000655",
          "label": "Wheel alignment inspection",
          "resolved": true
        },
        {
          "id": "R000643",
          "label": "Rack Guide Adjustment",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Avoid low-friction surfaces to be inspected, such as oil spilled on the floor or painted floor surfaces wet with water."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "If above standard value, Inspect steering coupling and Wheel alignment inspection and if there are no abnormalities Rack Guide Adjustment (1) The company shall",
